                    name="Video"
                    overlayButtonFontIcon="play"
                    overlayButtonIconKind="icon-font"
                    overlayButtonLabel="Watch 2:22"
                    overlayDescription="-"
                    overlayHeading="Navigating Ulcerative Colitis as a Child"
                    placeholderImage="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:297dee33-6b48-4e8c-8a10-052c54ed2965/as/maxresdefault.jpg"
                    placeholderImageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    posterAccessibilityLabel="Photo collage of Marissa and her husband"
                    projectNumber="-"
                    uri="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9dPIZT6-2so?enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com&amp;widgetid=1&amp;forigin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com%2Fwho-we-are%2Four-stories%2Fnavigating-ulcerative-colitis-as-a-child.html&amp;aoriginsup=1&amp;vf=1"
                    videoContentLayout="none"/>
                <block_3
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Her mother, who was a big advocate for her health being her caregiver and parent, quickly got her to a gastroenterologist. At her exam, there was blood which then led to a colonoscopy and a diagnosis, but Troy knows not everyone’s journey to an answer is as quick. “I’m grateful for my parents, but even with their help there were still a lot of unknowns,” says Troy. “Today my relationship with my doctor is different because I understand my body and I’m willing to share more.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_3>
                <block_4
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Building healthy relationships"
                    titleType="h2"/>
                <block_5
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Troy has had 15 abdominal surgeries including the removal of her colon, and now lives with a permanent ostomy. Her IBD sent her life in directions she never imagined. It also led her to find love.&lt;/p>&lt;p>“I had a friend that was going to an IBD event, a fundraiser, and I had never been to one before,” describes Frank Garufi, who at the time was a single father to a son with Crohn’s disease. He made the nearly 4-hour drive where he was drawn to Troy the moment he entered the room, and their connection quickly grew deep.&lt;/p>&lt;p>“Prior to meeting Marisa, there was a point in time where I felt like I was the only person in the world who was going through this,” says Garufi. His son developed IBD symptoms at just 2-months-old. “I kept going from doctor, to doctor, to doctor, trying to figure out what is going on here? What's wrong with my son?”&lt;/p>&lt;p>Garufi says it took more than three years for his son’s diagnosis, but it came when they finally visited gastroenterologists at a prominent IBD center. “We got to a place where they truly understood what this disease was like and were on the forefront of doing research and development into IBD.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_5>
                <block_6
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Connecting with the IBD community"
                    titleType="h2"/>
                <block_7
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Today the couple are grateful to the scientists who have persevered in researching the chronic disease, applying new learnings to the care for children living with IBD. Along with the gratitude, they help raise awareness of IBD by sharing their experiences. Troy and Garufi both blog about their respective stories as a young person living with ulcerative colitis and a caregiver to a child with Crohn’s disease.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_7>
                <block_8
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analyticsInteractionId="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    caption="\0"
